<FILEID>AP-NR-01-31-89 0114EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r a PM-NightStalker-List     01-31 0277</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Night Stalker-List,0287</SECOND>
<HEAD>Richard Ramirez Accused Of 13 Night Stalker Slayings</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Night Stalker, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Richard Ramirez is charged with 13 ``Night
Stalker'' slayings, along with 30 other felonies, including
attempted murder, rape and assault. Here is a list of the murder
victims referred to Monday in prosecutors' opening arguments:
   _June 1984: Jennie Vincow, 79, of Eagle Rock, killed during an
apparent burglary at her home, found with her throat slashed.
   _March 17, 1985: Dale Okazaki, 34, of Rosemead, found shot to
death in her condominium. A roommate, Marie Hernandez, was wounded
but survived.
   _March 17, 1985: Tsai-lian Yu, 30, of Monterey Park, apparently
pulled from her car and shot repeatedly around midnight.
   _March 27, 1985: Vincent Zazzara, 64, and Maxine Zazzara, 44, of
Whittier, found dead in their home.
   _May 14, 1985: William Doi, 66, of Monterey Park, killed at his
home.
   _May 29, 1985: Mabel Close Bell, 83, of Monrovia, fatally
bludgeoned in her home. Her invalid sister, Florence Lang, 80,
survived the attack.
   _July 1, 1985: Mary Louise Cannon, 75, of Arcadia, found in her
ransacked home beaten and with her throat slit.
   _July 7, 1985: Joyce Nelson, 60, of Monterey Park, killed at her
home.
   _July 20, 1985: Maxon Kneiding, 68, and his wife, Lela Kneiding,
64, of Glendale, killed at their home.
   _July 20, 1985: Chainarong Khovananth, 32, of Sun Valley, shot to
death while asleep in his home during a $30,000 burglary. His
29-year-old wife and their 8-year-old son survived beatings and
sexual attacks.
   _Aug. 8, 1985: Elyas Abowath, 35, of Diamond Bar, shot to death
in his home. His 28-year-old wife was raped and assaulted.
</TEXT>
