<SECOND>PM-Thailand-Crash,0162</SECOND>
<HEAD>Seven Killed In Copter Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAK,Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Seven army personnel including two officers
were killed when an army helicopter crashed in a jungled valley near
the Thai-Burmese border, a police officer said today.
   The transport helicopter was traveling from Mae Sot district of
this border province to a nearby military base in Phitsanulok
province, said Lt. Col. Lamchuan Keotai, Tak's deputy police chief.
   Lamchuan quoted hilltribes people as saying they saw the
helicopter catch fire before plunging to the valley floor.
   The officer quoted the pilot as informing the control tower in
Tak province by radio that due to heavy fog over the mountains he
would increase his altitude from 2,200 feet to 2,500 feet. Contact
was then lost with the craft.
   The cause of the crash was under investigation, the officer said.
   A rescue team including two helicopters and two L-19
reconnaissance aircraft found the wreckage in a densely forested
valley, Lamchuan said.
