<DOCNO> AP890131-0050 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-01-31-89 0514EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i PM-China-Shooting     01-31 0307</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-China-Shooting,0316</SECOND>
<HEAD>Track Athletes Kill Six, Wound One In Fujian</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Two track-and-field athletes using starter pistols
killed six people and wounded another for unknown reasons before
police killed one of them in a shootout, a newspaper reported today.
   The official China Sports Daily said 300 armed police officers
surrounded a building in the sports center in the southern city of
Fuzhou on Monday and exchanged shots with Shang Weidong, a 110-meter
hurdler, and Li Zhichuan, who specializes in the decathlon.
   Shang died in the shootout and Li was wounded, the newspaper said.
   The incident began Sunday morning when Shang and Li met three
acquaintances and asked them for $540. The report said it was not
clear why the two men asked for the money, but their request was
refused.
   An official at the Fuzhou city police department said ``women
were involved in the incident'' but declined to elaborate. China has
recently seen a rise in prostitution, especially in the richer
cities along the country's coast.
   The pair went to the room of their three acquaintances later that
afternoon, crashed through the door and began firing, killing the
three acquaintances, the paper said.
   The pair then locked themselves in the room. A short while later,
two men and two women entered.
   Li and Shang killed three of them and seriously wounded the
woman, the paper said. They then fled to the provincial sports
center, where several close friends, also track-and-field athletes,
helped them hide.
   Early Monday morning, police found Li and Shang hiding in the
attic of the five-story building. After a stand-off of almost three
hours, police killed Shang and captured Li in a quick shootout, the
report said.
   It was not clear how Li and Shang obtained live ammunition for
the starter pistols as it can not legally be bought in China.
</TEXT>
