<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``It's a sad day for the kids who are being abused in this
country.'' _ Dr. Vincent Fontana, chairman of the New York City
Mayor's Task Force on Child Abuse, on Joel Steinberg's conviction of
manslaughter _ but not murder _ in the beating death of his
6-year-old adoptive daughter.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``I appeal to the sensibility and honesty of all Nicaraguans so
this proposal doesn't turn into a political confrontation.
Otherwise, we'll be paying with the blood and the future of our
people.'' _ Nicaraguan President Daniel Ortega, calling for public
sacrifice in announcing an austerity plan to deal with his nation's
economic crisis.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``My neighbors say it is sacrilege, unpatriotic and everything
else.'' _ North Dakota farmer Luther Berntson, testifying at a
Department of Agriculture hearing in Washington on how he locked
away his plow in practicing a relatively new form of farming called
low-input agriculture.
