<HEAD>Girl Dropped From Second Flood Window Caught By Passerby</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman dropped her 4-year-old daughter from a
second-story window, but the child was caught by a passerby and was
uninjured.
   ``I told her, `Don't do it. Don't drop the baby,''' Melvin
Ashley, 25, said he told the mother Monday. ``But then she just
dropped her, and she (the child) fell right in my arms.
   ``I asked her if she was all right and then she stopped crying.''
   Authorities said the mother was taken to the Milwaukee County
Mental Health Complex for observation, and the 4-year-old and two
siblings were being cared for by the Milwaukee County Department of
Social Services.
   Ashley said he was walking down a street when he heard glass
breaking.
   ``She (the childen's mother) was throwing dressing drawers and
stuff out the window,'' he said.
   Ashley said he then saw the woman hold the 4-year-old out the
window by her legs.
   He positioned himself under the window as a crowd of 10 to 20
people gathered on the street and tried to persuade the woman not to
drop the child.
   The girl was covered with blood when she landed in his arms but
she was not cut anywhere, Ashley said.
   The blood ``must have been from the woman when she broke all the
windows,'' he said.
   Ashley said a neighbor took the child while he called police.
   ``I was just glad I was there to help her,'' Ashley said.
