<FIRST>r a AM-People     01-31 0539</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People,0561</SECOND>
<HEAD>People in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY44</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RADNOR, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actor Tommy Lee Jones insisted on doing his
own stunt work during the 16-week production of the CBS miniseries
``Lonesome Dove,'' much to the producer's distress.
   The four-part show, which starts Sunday, focuses on a 2,500-mile
cattle drive. Jones plays the drive leader, Captain Call, in the
production based on Larry McMurtry's Pulitzer Prize-winning novel.
   In the Feb. 4 issue of TV Guide, producer Dyson Lovell said he
feared Jones would get hurt atop a bucking horse, even though the
native Texan raises cattle and horses on his ranch.
   But Jones told Lovell he wanted to ride.
   ``If I don't, you get half a performance,'' he told the producer.
   ``Silver Spoon'' star Ricky Schroder, who at 18 is appearing in
his first adult role, said he spent three weeks in Texas learning
cowboy skills.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   English schoolgirl Elizabeth Ashcroft said she
turned the tables on pop star Michael Jackson by presenting him with
a T-shirt bearing the slogan ``I've met Elizabeth Ashcroft.''
   Elizabeth, 12, won a contest to attend one of Jackson's concerts
in Los Angeles last week and to meet him backstage.
   ``The T-shirt was my own idea,'' she said Tuesday. ``I've got
hundreds of things with his name on, so I thought he would like
something with mine.''
   Elizabeth, from Stourbridge, said she got a thank you and a hug
from Jackson.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>ATHENS, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dimitra Liani, the girlfriend of Premier
Andreas Papandreou, says she longs for the moment when Greeks will
accept her.
   Ms. Liani, 34, has come under heavy criticism from Greek
politicians and newspapers since she began appearing in public with
the 69-year-old Papandreou three months ago and he announced he
would divorce his wife.
   ``I believe that at some point the Greek people, with their sense
of justice, won't stick by this picture that they have of me,'' said
the tall, blond former stewardess in her first interview, published
in the latest Greek edition of the French magazine Marie Claire.
   Newspapers daily ridicule the premier's relationship with the
twice-divorced Ms. Liani, while there is a growing feeling among
Greeks that the love affair is making them look ridiculous abroad.
   Papandreou announced in October he intended to end his 37-year
marriage to his American-born wife, Margaret. The former Margaret
Chant of Elmhurst, Ill., married Papandreou in 1951 when he was a
junior economics professor at the University of Minnesota.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Alan Parker, who brought the controversial
civil rights film ``Mississippi Burning'' to the screen, was one of
five directors nominated Tuesday for the Directors Guild of America
award for outstanding achievement.
   Also named for work on 1988 movies were Charles Crichton,
director of ``A Fish Called Wanda''; Barry Levinson, ``Rain Man'';
Robert Zemeckis, ``Who Framed Roger Rabbit''; and Mike Nichols,
``Working Girl.''
   Clint Eastwood, who won a Golden Globe for best director
Saturday, wasn't among the nominees, who are chosen by a vote of
their peers.
   ``I was hoping Clint Eastwood would be nominated this year, but
he wasn't,'' said director Steven Spielberg, who announced the
nominations at a news conference at the guild's headquarters.
   The winner will be announced March 11.
</TEXT>
