<HEAD>New Navy Commander Appointed</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: ADDS one graf with explanation of ranks.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Brig. Gen. Micha Ram has been appointed
commander of the Israeli navy, the military command announced
Tuesday.
   Ram will assume the post Wednesday and will be promoted to the
rank of major general, it said. Ram replaces Maj. Gen. Abraham
Even-Shoshan.
   Ram, 47, has held a variety of Navy posts and has served as a
naval attache at the Israeli Embassy in Washington, the military
command said.
   During the 1973 Middle East war, Ram commanded the Reshef, the
first missile fast patrol boat in the Israeli navy. During the
1982-85 invasion and occupation of Lebanon, he headed navy
intelligence and was later appointed deputy commander of the navy.
   Ram is married and has two daughters, one of whom is a navy
officer.
   The ranks in the Israeli army and navy are the same.
