<SECOND>AM-Israel-Defector, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0744,0316</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jewish Soviet Scientist Defects To Israel, Officials Say</HEAD>
<HEAD>EDS: LEADS throughout to UPDATE with detail, background. No pickup.
Adds byline.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By SERGEI SHARGORODSKY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Soviet Jewish scientist who disappeared in
Paris and was reported as a defector by French diplomats has arrived
in Israel, the Foreign Ministry said Tuesday.
   ``All I can say is that Mr. Yakov Kogan has arrived in Israel a
few days ago. I am not aware of the circumstances of his arrival,''
Foreign Ministry spokesman Alon Liel said.
   French diplomatic sources said Tuesday that Kogan, a member of
the Soviet Academy of Sciences who had been in Paris for a seminar
on telecommunications, dropped from sight over the weekend and was
seeking asylum in Israel.
   Liel declined comment about Kogan's reported defection and said
he did not know where Kogan arrived from.
   Radio Shalom, a Jewish FM station in Paris, said Kogan is a
mathematician who participated in a seminar sponsored by the French
Foreign Ministry and disappeared Sunday. He was to have returned to
the Soviet Union on Tuesday.
   Israel Television quoted French sources as saying Kogan
approached Israeli representatives in Paris last week in a ``direct
or indirect way.''
   It said the Israelis consulted with the Foreign Ministry in
Jerusalem and decided that their consulate in Paris would issue a
tourist visa for Kogan, a standard procedure for every Jew who asks
to immigrate to Israel.
   Immediately afterwards, officials of the Jewish Agency ordered a
plane ticket for Kogan, again a customary procedure regarding a Jew
who cannot fund a ticket, the television said.
   There was no immediate response from the Soviet Union, which cut
diplomatic ties with Israel following the 1967 Middle East war.
Israel has demanded the right of free emigration for every Jew
wishing to live in the Jewish state.
</TEXT>
