<FIRST>r a AM-People-Shepherd     01-31 0137</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-People-Shepherd,0141</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cybill Shepherd and Husband Separate After Two-Year Marriage</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Actress Cybill Shepherd, who plays witty
detective Maddie Hayes on TV's ``Moonlighting,'' has separated from
her husband after two years of marriage, her publicist said Tuesday.
   ``Actress Cybill Shepherd and her husband Bruce Oppenheim
separated today,'' publicist Cheryl Kagen said in a brief statement
announcing the split. No reason was given.
   The couple were married March 1, 1987, and they have 1-year-old
twins, Ariel and Zachariah. Custody of the children wasn't being
disclosed, Ms. Kagen said.
   Miss Shepherd, 39, lives in Los Angeles and has custody of her
9-year-old daughter, Clementine, from a previous marriage. Oppenheim
is a chiropractor.
   The model-turned-actress, who stars with Bruce Willis in
``Moonlighting,'' appears with Ryan O'Neal in the movie ``Chances
Are,'' due for release March 10.
