<HEAD>Gibson Greetings Chairman Retiring</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CINCINNATI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gibson Greetings Inc., one of the nation's
largest greeting cards companies, said its chairman, Thomas J.
Cooney, will retire on Feb. 28.
   Benjamin J. Sottile, president and chief executive officer, will
assume the additional job of chairman March 1. Cooney, who had been
chairman for two years and president-CEO for about nine years before
that, has been named chairman emeritus.
   Cooney, 62, pioneered open greeting card displays and introduced
Mickey Mouse and Garfield the Cat as marketing innovations.
   Before the display system was introduced retailers routinely kept
their stock in fixture drawers where they could not be seen by
potential buyers.
