<DOCNO> AP890131-0252 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-01-31-89 1045EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-Unocal     01-31 0242</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-Unocal,0250</SECOND>
<HEAD>Unocal Earnings Up Strongly</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Unocal Corp.'s earnings expanded nearly
five-fold in the final three months of 1988, in part because of
improved earnings from refining and marketing operations and a $98
million after-tax gain on the sale of the company's downtown
headquarters, the company reported.
   The company said Monday other factors contributing to the rise
included increased gains from asset sales and improved chemicals
earnings.
   For the fourth quarter, after-tax profit totaled $141 million, or
$1.21 a share, on revenue of $2.6 billion. That compared with
earnings of $29 million, or 26 cents a share, on revenue of $2.3
billion in the same period in 1987.
   Profits for all of 1988 rose 165 percent to $480 million, or
$4.12 a share, from $181 million, or $1.56 a share in 1987.
   Unocal President and Chief Executive Officer Richard J.
Stegemeier said the stronger earnings were the result of higher
demand for refined products and improved product margins, although
there was some margin slippage at the end of the year.
   The 1988 results also include a $33 million after-tax refund for
overpayment of windfall profit tax and a $13 million gain from the
settlement of certain pension obligations, Stegemeier said.
   He said the company's refining, marketing and transportation
segment recorded earnings of $182 million in 1988, up from $42
million in 1987. For the fourth quarter, earnings were $58 million,
up from $14 million the previous year.
</TEXT>
