<FIRST>r f BC-StarSignal     01-31 0132</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-StarSignal,0138</SECOND>
<HEAD>Company Announces Full-Color Fax Machine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMPBELL, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   StarSignal Inc. has introduced what it
said is the first facsimile machine capable of sending full-color
pictures over conventional telephone lines.
   The company said Monday that the device, with a $19,000 price
tag, will be aimed at the growing desktop publishing market and
other uses that require fast transmission of color images. The
transmitted image could be printed out or electronically stored on
the other end.
   The new ``Colorfax'' system, which includes a color scanner,
color printer, data compression device and high-speed modem, can
scan any color document and reproduce it in 256,000 color
combinations, said StarSignal President Robert Widergren.
   After several weeks of testing the device, the company will start
shipping the unit in quantity in March, Widgren said.
</TEXT>
