<FILEID>AP-NR-01-31-89 2201EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f BC-HolidayCorp.     01-31 0195</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Holiday Corp.,0203</SECOND>
<HEAD>Holiday Corp. Sells Hotels</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Holiday Corp. has sold five Holiday Inn
hotels for $123 million and plans to transfer ownership of three
others worth $60 million, the company said Tuesday.
   The hotels were sold to a limited partnership, Holiday Pacific
Partners, and Holiday Corp. will continue to run them under a
property management agreement, the company said.
   The hotels are in north Lexington, Ky.; east Memphis; on the
Riverwalk in San Antonio, Texas; in north Cincinnati, Ohio; and in
the university area of South Bend, Ind.
   Holiday Pacific Partners also is to take over three other Holiday
Corp. hotels in April, the Memphis company said.
   Holiday Corp. said the hotel sales are part of the company's
continuing program for reducing its capital outlay while
concentrating on property management.
   The company announced plans in 1987 to sell off assets to
generate $900 million in after-tax proceeds as part of an overall
financial recapitalization.
   ``Even though we have more hotel assets yet to sell during the
remainder of this year, this transaction effectively completes the
execution of our recapitalization plan,'' said Michael D. Rose,
Holiday Corp.'s chief executive officer.
</TEXT>
